Creamy Corn Pasta With Basil
============================

**By** [**Melissa Clark**](https://cooking.nytimes.com/author/melissa-clark)
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

**![Creamy Corn Pasta With Basil](data:image/jpeg;base64,)**

Watch

Andrew Scrivani for The New York Times

**Total Time**

30 minutes

**Rating**

5(9,860)

**Comments**

[Read 1,000 comments](https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1018212-creamy-corn-pasta-with-basil#notes_section)

Theres no cream in this wonderfully summery pasta dish, just a luscious sauce made from pured fresh corn and sweet sauted scallions, along with Parmesan for depth and red chile flakes for a contrasting bite. Be sure to add the lemon juice and fresh herbs at the end; the rich pasta really benefits from their bright, fresh flavors. And while this is best made at the height of corn season, its still quite good even with out-of-season supermarket ears, or with frozen corn.
